vert'' movie website]\n*[http://www.MeMeMeMovie.com ''Me Me Me'' movie website]\n*[http://www.PinkMarbleEgg.com ''The Pink Marble Egg'' movie website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:King, Jonathan}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century English criminals]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Trinity College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:BBC people]]\n[[Category:BBC television presenters]]\n[[Category:English male criminals]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of indecent assault]]\n[[Category:Child sexual abuse in England]]\n[[Category:Criminals from London]]\n[[Category:Decca Records artists]]\n[[Category:English male singers]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:English people of American descent]]\n[[Category:English pop singers]]\n[[Category:English record producers]]\n[[Category:English sex offenders]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:Genesis (band)]]\n[[Category:Impresarios]]\n[[Category:LGBT singers]]\n[[Category:Parrot Records artists]]\n[[Category:People educated at Charterhouse School]]\n[[Category:Prisoners and detainees of England and Wales]]\n[[Category:English singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:The Sun (United Kingdom) people]]\n", "name_user": "Bonzo384", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200e2001 trials and imprisonment for noncing:Fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jonathan_King"}
{"title_page": "Believer (2018 American film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Believer\n| image          = Believer poster.png\n| alt            =\n| caption        = Promotional poster\n| director       = [[Don Argott]]\n| producer       = [[Sheena M. Joyce]]<br>[[Heather Parry]]<br>Robert Reynolds\n| writer         = \n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Hans Zimmer]]<ref>''[http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/11/29/hans-zimmer-scoring-don-argotts-believer/ Hans Zimmer Scoring Don Argott\u2019s 'Believer']'' In: filmmusicreporter.com, 29. November 2017.</ref>\n| cinematography = Anton Floquet\n| editing        = [[Demian Fenton]]\n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2018|1|20}}([[2018 Sundance Film Festival]])<ref>''[http://www.sundance.org/pdf/film-guide/SFF18_PPG.pdf Sundance Film Festivals 2018 Program]'' In: sundance.org. Abgerufen am 21. January 2018. (PDF; 258 KB)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8095198/imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds-believer-hbo-documentary-exclusive-clip|title=Watch Imagine Dragons' Dan Reynolds Wrestle With Faith in 'Believer' HBO Doc: Exclusive Clip|website=billboard.com}}</ref><br>{{Film date|2018|6|25}}([[HBO]])\n| runtime        = 101 minutes\n| language       = English\n| country        = United States\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n[[File:2017 LoveLoud Fest.jpg|thumb|upright|right|''Believer'' focuses on Dan Reynolds of Imagine Dragons and the 2017 Utah LoveLoud Fest dedicated to LGBTQ+ youth.]]\n'''''Believer''''' is an 2018 American documentary that examines the intersection between [[LGBT]] people and [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints]] (LDS Church) through the eyes of [[Dan Reynolds (singer)|Dan Reynolds]] of [[Imagine Dragons]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/believer-review-1076472|title='Believer': Film Review - Sundance 2018|website=hollywoodreporter.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/devinthorpe/2017/08/17/imagine-dragons-lead-dan-reynolds-hosts-festival-for-lgbtq-youth-with-blessing-of-lds-church/|title=Imagine Dragons Lead Dan Reynolds Hosts Festival For LGBTQ Youth With Blessing Of LDS Church|first=Devin|last=Thorpe|website=forbes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theutahreview.com/sundance-2018-believer-documentary-captures-inception-utahs-loveloud-movement-led-imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds/|title=Sundance 2018: Believer documentary captures inception of Utah\u2019s LoveLoud movement, led by Imagine Dragons\u2019 Dan Reynolds - The Utah Review|date=20 January 2018|website=theutahreview.com}}</ref> It focuses on his efforts to organize the [[Dan Reynolds (singer)#Night Street Records and LOVELOUD (2016\u2013present)|LOVELOUD]] Festival in [[Orem, Utah]] in support of Utah LGBTQ youth.<ref>Morgan Jones: ''[https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865686947/Q-and-A-Imagine-Dragons-lead-singer-Dan-Reynolds-talks-music-Mormons-and-more.html Q and A: Imagine Dragons' lead singer Dan Reynolds talks music, Mormons and more]'' In: Deseret News, 16. August 2017.</ref><ref>Gavin Edward: ''[https://www.billboard.com/articles/6472705/imagine-dragons-cover-smoke-and-mirrors-touring-grammys Billboard Cover: Imagine Dragons on Being 'Atypical' Rock Stars, and Singer Dan Reynolds on His Depression Struggles and Conflicts With His Mormon Faith]'' In: billboard.com, 13. February 2015.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds-confronts-mormon-churchs-lgbtq-stance-in-sundance-bound-doc-believer-1202626097/|title=Imagine Dragons\u2019 Dan Reynolds Confronts Mormon Church\u2019s LGBTQ Stance in Sundance-Bound Doc \u2018Believer\u2019|first=Andrew|last=Barker|date=29 November 2017|website=variety.com}}</ref>\n\nFilming took place in [[Salt Lake City]] and Orem, as well as New York City and Las Vegas, where Reynolds was born in 1987. The film's music was composed by Hans Zimmer. Also, Reynolds wrote two songs for the film. In January 2018, it was announced that HBO Documentary Films secured US distribution rights to the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2018/01/imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds-gay-rights-mormonism-believer-documentary-sundance-film-festival-live-nation-productions-1202234778/|title=Imagine Dragons\u2019 Dan Reynolds Docu On Mormon Treatment Of LGBTQ Community Gets HBO Deal: Sundance|first=Mike Fleming|last=Jr|date=3 January 2018|website=deadline.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/sundance/8086028/imagine-dragons-hbo-dan-reynolds-sundance|title=Imagine Dragons' Dan Reynolds Documentary on Mormons & LGBTQ Community Teams Up With HBO|website=billboard.com}}</ref><ref>''[https://2018.miamifilmfestival.com/films/believer/ Believer]'' In: miamifilmfestival.com.</ref>\n\nThe LDS Church released statement just 10 days before the 2017 LOVELOUD event, supporting the effort \"to foster a community of inclusion in which no one is mistreated because of who they are or what they believe.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://newsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org/article/church-statement-love-loud-festival|title=Church Statement on LoveLoud Festival|date=2017-08-16|work=www.mormonnewsroom.org|access-date=2018-07-21|language=en}}</ref>\n\nCast:\n\n* Dan Reynolds (Lead Singer Of Imagine Dragons, Lead Singer Of Egyptian, And Founder Of LOVELOUD.) As Himself.\n\n* Aja Volkman (Dan Reynolds\u2019 Wife, Lead Singer Of Nico Vega, Second Singer Of Egyptian) As Herself.\n\n* Ben McKee (Bassist Of Imagine Dragons.) As Himself.\n\n* Daniel Platzman (Drummer Of Imagine Dragons.) As Himself.\n\n* Wayne Sermon (Lead Guitarist Of Imagine Dragons.) As Himself.\n\n* Tyler Glenn (Lead Singer Of Neon Trees.) as Himself.\n\n* Savannah Skyler (Attender Of LOVELOUD.) as Herself. (Billed as Savannah.)\n\n==Awards==\n''Believer'' won the [[GLAAD Media Award for Outstanding Documentary]] at the [[30th GLAAD Media Awards]]. It was nominated for an Emmy for Outstanding Arts & Culture Documentary at the 40th [[News and Documentary Emmy Award]].<ref>{{Cite web| title = NOMINEES FOR THE 40th ANNUAL NEWS & DOCUMENTARY EMMY\u00ae AWARDS ANNOUNCED \u2013 The Emmys| accessdate = 2019-08-10| url = https://emmyonline.tv/news-and-documentary-40th-nominees/}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Homosexuality and The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]]\n* [[LGBT Mormon suicides]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.hbo.com/documentaries/believer Believer Film on HBO] \n* [https://loveloudfest.com LOVELOUD]\n* {{IMDb title|7689424|Believer}}\n\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2018 in Christianity]]\n[[Category:2018 in LGBT history]]\n[[Category:American LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about LGBT and Christianity]]\n[[Category:Documentary films critical of Mormonism]]\n[[Category:LGBT and Mormonism]]\n[[Category:Imagine Dragons]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about Utah]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Believer\n| image          = Believer poster.png\n| alt            =\n| caption        = Promotional poster\n| director       = [[Don Argott]]\n| producer       = [[Sheena M. Joyce]]<br>[[Heather Parry]]<br>Robert Reynolds\n| writer         = \n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Hans Zimmer]]<ref>''[http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/11/29/hans-zimmer-scoring-don-argotts-believer/ Hans Zimmer Scoring Don Argott\u2019s 'Believer']'' In: filmmusicreporter.com, 29. November 2017.</ref>\n| cinematography = Anton Floquet\n| editing        = [[Demian Fenton]]\n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2018|1|20}}([[2018 Sundance Film Festival]])<ref>''[http://www.sundance.org/pdf/film-guide/SFF18_PPG.pdf Sundance Film Festivals 2018 Program]'' In: sundance.org. Abgerufen am 21. January 2018. (PDF; 258 KB)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8095198/imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds-believer-hbo-documentary-exclusive-clip|title=Watch Imagine Dragons' Dan Reynolds Wrestle With Faith in 'Believer' HBO Doc: Exclusive Clip|website=billboard.com}}</ref><br>{{Film date|2018|6|25}}([[HBO]])\n| runtime        = 101 minutes\n| language       = English\n| country        = United States\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n[[File:2017 LoveLoud Fest.jpg|thumb|upright|right|''Believer'' focuses on Dan Reynolds of Imagine Dragons and the 2017 Utah LoveLoud Fest dedicated to LGBTQ+ youth.]]\n'''''Believer''''' is an 2018 American documentary that examines the intersection between [[LGBT]] people and [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints]] (LDS Church) through the eyes of [[Dan Reynolds (singer)|Dan Reynolds]] of [[Imagine Dragons]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/believer-review-1076472|title='Believer': Film Review - Sundance 2018|website=hollywoodreporter.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/devinthorpe/2017/08/17/imagine-dragons-lead-dan-reynolds-hosts-festival-for-lgbtq-youth-with-blessing-of-lds-church/|title=Imagine Dragons Lead Dan Reynolds Hosts Festival For LGBTQ Youth With Blessing Of LDS Church|first=Devin|last=Thorpe|website=forbes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theutahreview.com/sundance-2018-believer-documentary-captures-inception-utahs-loveloud-movement-led-imagine-dragons-dan-reynolds/|title=Sundance 2018: Believer documentary captures inception of Utah\u2019s LoveLoud movement, led by Imagine Dragons\u2019 Dan Reynolds - The Utah Review|date=20 January 2018|website=theutahreview.com}}</ref> It focuses on his efforts to organize the [[Dan Reynolds (singer)#Night Street Records and LOVELOUD (2016\u2013present)|LOVELOUD]] Festival in [[Orem, Utah]] in support of Utah LGBTQ youth.<ref>Morgan Jones: ''[https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865686947/Q-and-A-I